CommonFields.Publication: Journal of Polymer Science Part B: Polymer Physics
CommonFields.Title: Functionalized graphene sheet-Poly(vinylidene fluoride) conductive nanocomposites
Author: Ansari, Seema
Giannelis, Emmanuel P.
CommonFields.Location: Department of Materials Science and Engineering, Cornell University, Ithaca, New York 14853

Drying-Evaporation.Description: The slurry was dried in a vacuum oven and kept in the oven until use.

ChooseParameter.Other: 0.2–0.3 g of GO powder is placed in an alumina boat
It is then inserted into a quartz tube that is sealed on one end
The other side is closed with a steel cap with an inlet and outlet for continuously passing argon gas that passes through at a rate of 5 cm^3/min
The tube is inserted into a Mellen two zone tubular furnace for 30 s at 1000 C
The graphite oxide is reduced and expanded to form FGS

Filler.Description: The funcitonalized graphene sheet was prepared with the graphite oxide slurry provided.

Mixing.Description: FGS was weighed and dispersed in DMF
The PVDF and DMF mixture was stirred for 30 mins

ChooseParameter.Other: composite solution was coagulated by adding water

Drying-Evaporation.Description: precipitated samples were dried in vacuum

MoldingInfo.Description: samples were prepared by compression molding using a 0.65-mm thick spacer

HeatingRate.description: samples were heated from 40 to 240 C with a ramp rate of 5 C/min
